olive oil
2 Potato
1 Tomato
1 packet Slivered Almonds
2 packet Beef Rump
1 packet Onion Chutney
1 packet spinach & rocket mix
1 packet balsamic glaze
1 Avocado

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into fries.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• Meanwhile, slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and thinly slice. Slice tomato into thin wedges. Roughly chop roasted almonds.
• Place beef rump between two sheets of baking paper. Pound beef with a meat mallet or rolling pin until slightly flattened. Season beef generously with salt and pepper.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook beef, turning, for 5-6 minutes (depending on thickness), or until cooked to your liking.

TIP: Cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded.
TIP: Pounding the beef ensures that it's extra tender once cooked.

• Reduce heat to medium, add onion chutney and a splash of water and turn to coat. Transfer to a plate to rest.

• In a medium bowl, combine avocado, tomato, spinach & rocket mix and balsamic & olive oil dressing. Season to taste.

• Slice beef rump.
• Divide sticky beef rump, avocado salad and potato fries between plates. Garnish salad with roasted almonds. Enjoy!